{"word":"πάγη","slug":"πάγη","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>πάγη</b></el> <el>(πά˘γη, ἡ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:πήγνυμι'><el>πήγνυμι</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>anything that fixes</i> or <i>fastens, a snare, noose, trap</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>: <i>a fowling-net</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>a trap, snare</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}